Situated by the small river 't Gein in Abcoude, just a 20-minute drive away from Amsterdam, lies Boerderij Groenewoud, a charming national monument with over 350 years of history.

With 5150 m² of private space, this farmhouse offers the best of both worlds: the serenity and beauty of the countryside combined with the proximity to Amsterdam. A truly ideal place for large families with a love for animals and the outdoors, with a romantic garden, stables for horses and sheep and a private dock directly on the river. An impressive office in the old carriage house also provides ample opportunity to work from home.

The location is ideal for families with children, with many schools nearby and Amsterdam at biking distance. The elegant renovation and modern additions make this farmhouse a unique and attractive family home, perfect for those who want to enjoy a warm and peaceful living environment in nature without giving up the convenience and excitement of the city. 

The intimate rooms, sloping roofs, and visible beams make the house’s ample 475 m² of living space feel like a warm family home. Meanwhile, the distinctive interior, which is eccentric yet harmonious, adds to the cozy atmosphere. 

As the former home of renowned interior designer Reineke Antvelink and her RA studio, this farmhouse is a true passion project; a masterful balance between extravagance and simplicity, full of surprising combinations of material, form, color, and style. The combination of pure materials such as wood, natural stone, and antiques, combined with fresh colors, patterns, and design, makes the interior youthful and lively without detracting from the authentic character of the home.

FARMHOUSE
GROUND FLOOR
After the romantic entrance, you walk through the lush greenery to the entrance of the farmhouse, located next to a large terrace. Inside, under the stairs, there is a convenient cloakroom, while on the right side there is a stylish pink guest toilet.
The front room, located above the wine and pantry cellar, serves as a cozy sitting room. Here, the family can gather around the fireplace to watch a movie, read a book, or play games together. The beautiful handmade wall cabinet on both sides of the fireplace contains a hidden door that provides access to the lower dining room and kitchen. This eat-in kitchen is designed for all-day enjoyment, with a cozy seating area that offers a lovely view of the garden. The old wooden beams and the eccentric tiled floor contribute to the charm of the space. The custom-made kitchen has received a unique facelift with a black marble countertop, green tiles from Piet Jonker, and modern built-in appliances, making it fully equipped without sacrificing country charm.
At the rear of the farmhouse in the barn, there is a spacious sitting room where guests can be entertained in style, with a beautiful bar and a tiled stove for warm comfort. This room also features a large glass wall with French doors overlooking the lush garden with long-stretched views over the meadows. The wooden roof structure, visible up to the ridge, is one of the unique elements in this atmospheric living space full of custom-made interior design elements.
The master bedroom and bathroom, both with large skylights on the north side, are equipped with beautiful elements such as thick oak beams, grass wallpaper, pink panel doors, and rustic stable windows that echo the monumental history.

FIRST FLOOR
The first floor impresses with its blend of authentic country living with modern comfort. The unusual length-to-width ratio makes the atmosphere  warm and homely. Meanwhile, a clever layout for the spacious bedrooms, with entrances tucked behind the study, enhances the living enjoyment. This rear room adjoins a mezzanine, closed off with a glass wall. Furthermore, on this floor, there is a bathroom, a separate toilet room, a laundry room, and various built-in wardrobes, ideal for large families or those who enjoy hosting guests.

CARRIAGE HOUSE
An indoor connection leads from the farmhouse to the carriage house, which on the ground floor offers an in-home office. This workspace, with a custom-made interior, benefits from beautiful light and has a stylish kitchen and toilet. The upper floor of the carriage house accommodates two fantastic bedrooms, a spacious mezzanine with custom-made wardrobes, a toilet room, and a beautifully decorated bathroom. Perfect for those who like to work from home, while the indoor connection also allows this building to be seamlessly integrated into the farmhouse for even more living space.

OUTBUILDINGS
In 2021, a large barn was built with high-quality materials, perfectly matching the farmhouse. The barn is completely insulated and equipped with underfloor heating. The roof, covered with 55 solar panels, contributes to the property's sustainability. This barn is suitable as a sports/relaxation space, workspace, or can be converted into a guesthouse. There is also access to a heated garage at the back. Next to the barn stands a charming octagonal stable with a thatched roof, equipped with beautiful stable windows, a walk-in stable, and spacious horse boxes, a must for equestrian enthusiasts that also provides an opportunity for even more recreational space.

EXTERIOR
The farmhouse, carriage house, and other external buildings are situated on a beautiful plot of 5150 m². This green oasis offers a serene living environment for both people and animals, surrounded by trees and breathtaking views of the adjacent meadows. At the front of the plot, on the river Gein, there is a private dock, ideal for a small boat or for swimming in the summer.

UNIQUE POINTS OF INTEREST
